People can see this is a real mercenary company now, and not a handful of wandering vagabonds."  HiYun declares.  "We trade in strength, and now that our numbers have gone up, so will our price."


"We trade in strength, and now that our numbers have gone up, so will our price."  It appears he has the right of it. You notice one particularly fat nobleman sizing up the company as if he already has a task in mind. The Usurper's Bane are now a force to be reckoned with. As the men head for the tavern to wash the road dust from their throats, the "full-throated" echoes of their song still bounce off the timber-framed houses. HiYun wipes a bit of grit from his brow, his eyes following that fat nobleman who was eyeing your line.

"The coin we spent on those recruits was an investment," HiYun mutters, leaning against a post near the town square. "But steel and grain aren't cheap with twelve mouths to feed. Let's see if that noble's purse is as heavy as he looks."

They aren't working together, Captainwe've just walked into a nightmare where the spiders are the hunters and that Champion is the wall we have to break through to escape."

The village headman is already approaching, nervously wringing a cap in his hands. He looks like a man with a problem and a very small purse to fix it with.

How would you like to spend the afternoon? Shall we talk to the headman to see if the stitchers have been sighted near the fields, check the marketplace for cheap grain to feed the twelve, or find a spot to train Theudebald before the sun goes down?

We replenished our food supply. Much of it was sold off in the last town to make a profit. Aside from that, there werent much happening in this village. HiYun doesn't even look her in the eye as he hands her a rusted spear. He just sighs and looks at you. "A widow and a vagabond. We're certainly building a company of the forgotten, Captain. Lets hope she remembers how to stand still when the screaming starts. Its a mercy, in a waybetter to die with a weapon in hand than starving in a gutter."

Theudebald nods a silent greeting to his fellow "purposeless" traveler. The company is now a strange mix of Vatt'ghern skill, Abyssal curses, and desperate souls destined for the front line.

Where shall we lead this flock of veterans and victims next? Do we continue the trek further North into the heart of the "stitcher" rumors, or is there a nearby landmark on the map you'd like to investigate while Hiltrude still has the strength to walk?

As we prepare to leave the village and continue the journey north, this happened:

With a cocky grin, The Butcher strolls into your tent like he owns the place.  "I need a favor. Ohnemenschen's got something of mine, but I'm not welcome here. Could you, uh, go shopping for me?"

He smiles.  "This will make you rich, my friend. You'll be paid 1500 crowns when the contract is done."

A wise instinct. 1,500 crowns for a "shopping trip" in a tiny farming village doesn't just smell like a trapit reeks of a death sentence. No butcher pays that kind of gold for sausages and spices unless the "goods" are illegal, immoral, or currently guarded by the local militia's heads on pikes.

HiYun watches the man swagger out of the tent after your refusal, his hand never leaving his sword pommel. "A man who smiles that wide while offering that much gold is looking for a scapegoat, not a partner," he spits. "Let him find some other fools to hang for his 'favors.' We have real monsters to hunt."

The men outside are already breaking camp. Hiltrude looks relieved to be leaving the village behindperhaps she feared the "favors" the Butcher had in mind involved people of her station. Theudebald just adjusts his pack, ready for more walking.

Current Status: Northward Bound

  • Decision: Declined "The Butcher's" suspicious contract.

  • Inventory: Food supplies replenished.

  • Time: Day 26, heading into the afternoon.

The road north stretches out before you, away from the deceptive "smiles" of Ohnemenschen and toward the grim reality of the stitchers. The path ahead grows colder as the elevation rises.

Shall we push hard through the evening to put distance between us and the Butcher, or would you like to scout the nearby woods for any of those "grafted" tracks before nightfall?

What a session! The Usurper's Bane has transformed from a wandering band into a formidableif slightly eccentriccompany of twelve (plus one). You've survived ancient horrors and mountain politics alike.

Session 8 Chronology: The Raven and the Stitchers

1. The Ascension of the Bane:

  • You assembled a full 12-man roster in Gipfelfeste, solidifying your status as a "real" mercenary company.

  • The Ritual: You bestowed the Ravens Mark on Godfrey. He gained dark Abyssal powers at the cost of his physical vitality, beginning his journey toward "blood purification."

2. The Delve into Blackwatch Keep:

  • Accepted a contract from a beast-clad Druid and Hallstein in Eisenstein to retrieve the Staff of Foresight.

  • Fought a brutal 7-round battle against Ancient Undead and Champion Mummies.

  • Casualty: Kaetherlen was pulverized into dust. The company returned victorious but mourning a brother.

3. The Birthday Blunder:

  • Hunted a "monstrous" threat outside Eisenstein: an unholy alliance of 14 Webknechts and a Champion Ancient Soldier.

  • NeCola dominated the field (550 damage), while Dauid "graduated" from fodder status by surviving a staggering 378 damage.

  • You ended the contract by flinging a giant spider corpse into Hallsteins birthday party, collecting 980 crowns in total.

4. Expanding the Ranks:

  • Moved North to Fuhrtmark, hearing rumors of Flesh Golems and mad Stitchers.

  • Recruited Theudebald (Vagabond) to fill the ranks and Hiltrude (Widow) as a desperate 13th member/fodder.

5. Moral Fortitude in Ohnemenschen:

  • Resupplied and wisely declined a suspicious 1,500-crown "favor" from The Butcher, avoiding a clear trap.

Current Company Ledger

  • Date: Day 26, Midday.

  • Roster: 13/12 (11 Veterans, 2 New Recruits).

  • Key Members: NeCola (Champion-Slayer), Dauid (The Unkillable), Godfrey (Cursed), HiYun (Right-hand).

  • Treasury: Strong (after the 780-crown payout and 200-crown advance).

  • Next Goal: Continuing North to find the source of the "Grafted Flesh" abominations.
